{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 12:10:15.490783", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nExecutive summary\\n- Network health: Critical. No host-to-host connectivity across the 10.0.0.0/24 data network.\\n- Primary anomaly: All Open vSwitch devices (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1) are configured in fail_mode=secure and are disconnected from the SDN controller at 20.0.0.100:6633 with “Connection refused.” With no controller and no local flows installed, all data-plane traffic (including ARP) is dropped.\\n- Fault localization: Control-plane/controller service at 20.0.0.100:6633. Physical links and host NICs appear healthy. Data-plane ports are up on all switches.\\n- Likely root cause: SDN controller not accepting OpenFlow connections (service not listening on TCP 6633), leaving OVS in secure mode without flows, which blocks all L2 forwarding.\\n\\nObserved symptoms and tests\\n- End-to-end reachability\\n  - All pings between hosts fail with 100% loss and “Destination Host Unreachable” from the source:\\n    - Examples:\\n      - host_1_1 -> 10.0.0.2/10.0.0.3/10.0.0.4: 4 tx, 0 rx, +4 errors, 100% loss\\n      - host_2_1 -> 10.0.0.4/10.0.0.2: 4 tx, 0 rx, +4 errors, 100% loss\\n- ARP resolution\\n  - ip neigh on hosts shows neighbor entries in FAILED state for all peers (e.g., 10.0.0.2, .3, .4). This indicates ARP requests are not being forwarded and/or responded to.\\n- Host interfaces\\n  - All hosts have correct IPs in 10.0.0.0/24 and “Link detected: yes.” RX packets remain 0 while TX increases, consistent with ARP requests not getting replies.\\n- Switch status and OpenFlow pipeline\\n  - OVS controller configuration on all switches:\\n    - target: tcp:20.0.0.100:6633\\n    - is_connected: false\\n    - status: state=BACKOFF, last_error=\"Connection refused\"\\n  - Fail mode on all bridges: secure\\n  - Flow tables on all bridges: empty (ovs-ofctl dump-flows shows no entries).\\n  - Switch ports toward hosts and inter-switch links show state LIVE at 10G full-duplex; no physical errors observed.\\n- Management network\\n  - leaf_1 has 20.0.0.2/24 (eth3), leaf_2 has 20.0.0.3/24 (eth3), spine_1 has 20.0.0.1/24 (eth2).\\n  - “Connection refused” implies TCP reachability to 20.0.0.100 exists but the OpenFlow service is not listening, differentiating it from a pure connectivity failure.\\n\\nFault localization\\n- Data-plane links:\\n  - Host-to-leaf and leaf-to-spine physical links are up (OVS port state LIVE, host NIC link detected).\\n  - No evidence of L1/L2 physical faults.\\n- Control plane:\\n  - Common failure across all switches: inability to connect to controller at 20.0.0.100:6633 with explicit “Connection refused.”\\n  - No flows present and fail_mode=secure prevents fallback switching, causing complete L2 forwarding loss including ARP.\\n\\nRoot cause analysis\\n- The SDN controller at 20.0.0.100 is not accepting OpenFlow connections on TCP 6633 (service closed/refusing). Because all OVS bridges are configured with fail_mode=secure and have empty flow tables, they drop all packets. Consequently, ARP requests from hosts do not propagate or receive replies, leading to neighbor resolution failures and “Destination Host Unreachable” for all intra-subnet traffic, even between hosts on the same leaf.\\n\\nImpact scope\\n- All switches: leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1.\\n- All hosts on 10.0.0.0/24: host_1_1, host_1_2, host_2_1, host_2_2.\\n- Complete loss of L2/L3 connectivity within the tenant subnet due to blocked ARP and data frames.\\n\\nSupporting evidence (key excerpts)\\n- Ping failures with “Destination Host Unreachable” and 100% loss from all sources.\\n- ip neigh on hosts: entries show FAILED for all peers.\\n- OVS controller status on all switches (ovs-vsctl list controller):\\n  - is_connected: false\\n  - status: last_error=\"Connection refused\", state=BACKOFF\\n  - target: tcp:20.0.0.100:6633\\n- OVS bridges: fail_mode: secure; flow tables empty (ovs-ofctl dump-flows).\\n- OVS ports: state LIVE on eth0/eth1/eth2 interfaces; no link errors; host NICs link detected yes.\\n\\nConclusion\\n- Abnormal condition confirmed: end-to-end data-plane failure across the topology.\\n- Fault localized to the SDN control plane endpoint at 20.0.0.100:6633 (controller not listening), not to physical links or host NICs.\\n- Root cause: Controller unavailability combined with OVS fail_mode=secure and absence of flows, resulting in universal packet drops and ARP failure., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='2d63d6a8-fdcc-4b01-8870-c6f66451e0d2'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
